d into a political party: the Farmers' Party. The main reason for this was that their position was not represented by any of the existing political parties in parliament. Other protest groups, in particular the direct action-oriented farmers and the progressive farmers' coalitions, appeared to be more successful in achieving their aims through existing political parties.
